From Don Graham Subject Re JEEP WRANGLER OPINI In article Tom Vervaeke writes I have had two Wranglers and still have the second right It's a Wrangler Base model with the big I engine hard top no power steering or air Runs like a Has about on Has never been in the I can change my own oil nice tall vehicle I can lube it myself fittings I occasionally take it to Jiffy Lube to check the differentials and do the oil change My previous Wrangler had nary a problem Here in Colorado there' more Jeeps than BMW's Mercedes Volvos and the like together In fact Jeep has been called the Colorado Car for a They hold their value well and are very easy to Mine cost right around Of course I didn't blow money on an Islander Sahara or Renegade which I have a Wrangler Sahara and paid new including the rebate are just Wranglers with fancy inside After driving a CJ for years that fancy stuff is pretty The cars are primitive ride like a dump truck But if you live in an area that gets around of snow per winter you'd have one They'll go anywhere with a winch and are easy to get parts The I like my Wrangler but when doing some serious off roading it can't keep up with a CJ because of ground clearance and limited suspension I do have a winch and would like to get an ARB air locker in the engine puts out HP and gets around Not I love the Just my I'm sure there are bad ones out there but that goes for any make and Don Graham